Map Your Salesforce Queues to Telephony Provider Queues

To route calls to a contact center queue, map the Salesforce queue to the telephony provider queue. Although you can define the routing logic using Salesforce queues, the routing actually takes place in the telephony system using the telephony provider queues. To ensure that calls are routed correctly, map the queues.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
Customize Application or Contact Center Admin

This feature is available with these telephony models:

SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

Create queues in Salesforce and your telephony system before proceeding. See Create Queues.

In Setup, enter Contact Centers in the Quick Find box. Click the contact center name for which you want to map queues. Under Queue Mapping, click Add. Map the Salesforce queue to the telephony provider's queue. The mapping appears under the Queue Mapping section in the contact center details page. To edit or delete a mapping, click the dropdown and select Edit or Delete.
